    "featured_collection_KGp9mK": {
      "type": "featured-collection",
      "settings": {
        "title": "Toilets",
        "heading_size": "h1",
        "description": "<p>Toilets are a core functional element of the bathroom, with modern design placing emphasis on efficiency, comfort, and ease of maintenance. Current preferences favour streamlined profiles and practical configurations that integrate cleanly into contemporary bathroom layouts while supporting everyday usability.<br/><br/>Wall-faced and back-to-wall toilets continue to be widely specified for their ability to conceal pipework, simplify cleaning, and create a more cohesive finish across the space. Rimless designs are increasingly preferred for hygiene and ease of maintenance, while soft-close seats contribute to quieter operation and improved day-to-day comfort. Water efficiency also remains a key consideration, with dual-flush systems supporting reduced water usage without compromising performance.<br/><br/>The New Year Sale includes toilet options from established manufacturers such as <a href=\"https://www.cookandbathe.com.au/collections/geberit\" title=\"https://www.cookandbathe.com.au/collections/geberit\">Geberit</a>, <a href=\"https://www.cookandbathe.com.au/collections/argent\" title=\"https://www.cookandbathe.com.au/collections/argent\">Argent</a>, <a href=\"https://www.cookandbathe.com.au/collections/villeroy-boch\" title=\"https://www.cookandbathe.com.au/collections/villeroy-boch\">Villeroy & Boch</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.cookandbathe.com.au/collections/fienza-toilets\" title=\"https://www.cookandbathe.com.au/collections/fienza-toilets\">Fienza</a>, offering a range of designs suited to modern residential bathrooms and renovation projects.<br/><br/>When selected with layout and usage in mind, toilets contribute to bathrooms that feel balanced, practical, and resolved, supporting long-term performance while aligning with contemporary expectations for efficiency and design clarity.<br/><br/></p>",
        "show_description": false,
        "description_style": "body",
